FNB Connect has launched once off Mega Data bundles which include a 50GB for R879 and 100GB for R1,399 – available from 1 December 2017. In October, FNB Connect announced that it would reward its customers with a windfall of 3.3 billion megabytes of data for using the bank’s digital platforms. The group said it has since seen a 65% increase in daily data usage, while the overall data usage has increased by 76% in November alone. “These bundles will be ideal for people who will be away on holiday and don’t have access to their traditional fibre or fixed LTE home offerings,” said chief commercial officer at FNB Connect, Shadrack Palmer. The data incentive runs till 31 January 2018. Read: FNB launches special iPhone X deal for credit customers